DN.SnS_ancientbottlegourd.seed.Description: Grown in Fall. Takes twelve days. Does not regrow.

DN.SnS_ancientgiantappleberry.Name: Ancient Giant Apple Berry
DN.SnS_ancientgiantappleberry.Description: It's unusually large. The outside is soft but the inside resembles an apple. Confusing, but tasty.

DN.SnS_ancientgiantappleberry.seed.Name: Ancient Giant Apple Berry
DN.SnS_ancientgiantappleberry.seed.Description: Grown in Spring, Summer, and Fall. Takes ten days. Does not regrow.

DN.SnS_ancientazuredetura.Name: Ancient Azure Detura Flower
DN.SnS_ancientazuredetura.Description: A dormant cousin of the Sunflower. It's very resilient, and can grow in the cold with minimal light.

DN.SnS_ancientazuredetura.seed.Name: Ancient Azure Detura Flower
DN.SnS_ancientazuredetura.seed.Description: Grown in Fall and Winter. Takes eight days. Does not regrow.

DN.SnS_ancientglowinghuckleberry.Name: Ancient Glowing Huckleberry
DN.SnS_ancientglowinghuckleberry.Description: A massive, juicy berry that faintly glows.

DN.SnS_ancientglowinghuckleberry.seed.Name: Ancient Glowing Huckleberry Seeds
DN.SnS_ancientglowinghuckleberry.seed.Description: Previously dormant, ancient and unrecognizable. Takes 28 days to produce a mature berry vine. Bears Huckleberries in the Summer and Fall. Only grows if the 8 surrounding 'tiles' are empty.

DN.SnS_ancientsweettealeaves.Name: Ancient Sweet Tea Leaves
DN.SnS_ancientsweettealeaves.Description: An unusual tea plant that grows best in extreme conditions. It brews sweet enough that it's liked even by people who don't favor tea.

DN.SnS_ancientsweettealeaves.seed.Name: Ancient Sweet Tea Bush Seeds
DN.SnS_ancientsweettealeaves.seed.Description: Grown in Summer and Winter. Takes thirteen days, regrows in four.

DN.SnS_adventureguildbadge.Description: The shield-shaped, hand-forged symbol of your guild membership. The number 23 is carved into the back.

DN.SnS_destykeychain.Name: Desty's Keychain
DN.SnS_destykeychain.Description: An unusual keychain for Long Live The King, in the shape of an X.

DN.SnS_paladinbook.Description: An emotional account of a Paladin's trip to a dark place.

DN.SnS_PallidSailfin.Description: A fish from the abyss, with ghostly fins that resemble sails.

DN.SnS_FiveLinedConstellationFish.Name: DN.SnS_FiveLinedConstellationFish

DN.SnS_GoldieTheBatteryPoweredFish.Description: How are there so many of these things?...

DN.SnS_DuskspireHeart.Name: Duskspire Heart
DN.SnS_DuskspireHeart.Description: The only untainted part of the Duskspire Behemoth... perhaps it's resilient to corruption!

Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Eerie_Plant_See.Name: Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Eerie_Plant_Seeds
Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Eerie_Plant_See.Description: Are you sure these will grow? It probably doesn't matter when you plant them

Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Ghost_Berry.Name: Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Ghost_Berry
Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Ghost_Berry.Description: This eerie fruit seems like it doesn't belong in our world

Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Giant_Old_Coin.Name: Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Giant_Old_Coin
Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Giant_Old_Coin.Description: This coin is huge! What a lucky find!

Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Old_Coin.Name: Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Old_Coin
Tarniyar.CP.WalkToDesert_Old_Coin.Description: Just because it's old doesn't mean it's valuable

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ancient_Music_Box.Name: Ancient Music Box
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ancient_Music_Box.Description: It plays a soft yet sweet tune. A faded text is engraved; 'mama esh'

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Arugula_Roll.Name: Arugula Roll
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Arugula_Roll.Description: Fresh arugula, bathing in spicy sauce and resting in a tortilla wrap.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Aurorean_Iris.Name: Aurorean Iris
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Aurorean_Iris.Description: 'I just want you to know who I am.' - Some singer, probably.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Autumn_Dew_Drop_Juice.Name: Autumn Dew Drop Juice
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Autumn_Dew_Drop_Juice.Description: The flavor of the mountains, contained in a single drink!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Autumn_Drop_Berry.Name: Autumn Drop Berry
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Autumn_Drop_Berry.Description: Tastes like rainy autumn nights. Commonly found near mountain ridges. Has a nutty, yet sweet taste.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Autumnal_Serenity.Name: Autumnal Serenity
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Autumnal_Serenity.Description: Pika's fall special. With every bite, you'll 'fall' in love.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Bladetail_Sturgeon.Name: Bladetail Sturgeon
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Bladetail_Sturgeon.Description: A very dangerous fish, with a tail as sharp as a blade. Overfishing caused this species' population to dwindle. Their tail may have served as arrowheads in ancient times.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Caped_Tree_Frog.Name: Caped Tree Frog
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Caped_Tree_Frog.Description: The red pattern that covers its neck and back looks like a cape. When leaping, it tucks one arm in while extending the other. Its rarity caused it to become a valuable pet among collectors.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Cardia_Septal_Jellyfish.Name: Cardia Septal Jellyfish
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Cardia_Septal_Jellyfish.Description: Truly a biological wonder. It bears a striking resemblance to the septum of a heart and the ventricles that connect it. Though poisonous, it is endangered because of its lack of mobility.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Cherry_Berry_Shakey.Name: Cherry Berry Shakey
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Cherry_Berry_Shakey.Description: A sweet, cherry-rich drink beloved by both kids and adults!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Cherry_Pluot.Name: Cherry Pluot
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Cherry_Pluot.Description: A sweet mixture of plum and apricot hybridizing with a foreign variant of cherry.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Clementine_Juice.Name: Clementine Juice
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Clementine_Juice.Description: A sweet juice made from the local forage.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Crimson_Spiked_Clam.Name: Crimson Spiked Clam
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Crimson_Spiked_Clam.Description: An endangered species of clam, covered with sharp red spikes. Fetches a mighty high price due to the ruby-like pearls it creates.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Cutthroat_Trout.Name: Cutthroat Trout
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Cutthroat_Trout.Description: The red patterns in its mouth make it look aggressive despite being docile.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Deep_Ridge_Angler.Name: Deep Ridge Angler
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Deep_Ridge_Angler.Description: A legendary fish found in the deep forest of the mountain. It's often mistaken for a phantom!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Desert_Tangelo.Name: Desert Tangelo
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Desert_Tangelo.Description: A seedless hybrid of tangerine and grapefruit that looks like it has been sun-kissed in the desert.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Elven_Comb.Name: Elven Comb
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Elven_Comb.Description: An ancient comb with embedded gems. The patterns sort of form the word 'Zango'.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ember_Blood_Lime.Name: Ember Blood Lime
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ember_Blood_Lime.Description: A relatively acidic fruit that's a cross breed of mandarin and lime which is suitable for sauces.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Entombed_Ring.Name: Entombed Ring
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Entombed_Ring.Description: The ring inside the gem seems to have a name engraved in it. The text 'sheku' can be barely read.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Everfrost_Stone.Name: Everfrost Stone
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Everfrost_Stone.Description: It's ice-cold to the touch! One may get frostbitten fingers just by holding it for too long.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Fairytale_Lionfish.Name: Fairytale Lionfish
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Fairytale_Lionfish.Description: A rare lionfish species. Its vibrant colors serve as camouflage. They hide within the coral reef in the Gem Sea. Rumors say these fish serve as an ingredient for an ancient love potion.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Fixer_Eel.Name: Fixer Eel
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Fixer_Eel.Description: A close relative of the electric eel. This variant is rarely found in rivers. It got its name from a local belief that its meat can heal any kind of sickness or sadness. Because of this belief, it suffers from overfishing.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Forage_Souffle.Name: Forage Souffle
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Forage_Souffle.Description: Keep quiet and nobody will explode.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Forest_Amancay.Name: Forest Amancay
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Forest_Amancay.Description: Only good vibes and sunshine are emitted by this flower!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Forest_Halva.Name: Forest Halva
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Forest_Halva.Description: A mixture of different local confections.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Foxbloom.Name: Foxbloom
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Foxbloom.Description: A mythical flower only thought to exist in legends. It gives off an otherwordly aura.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Freddie_s_Sword.Name: Freddie's Sword
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Freddie_s_Sword.Description: Freddie's sword! He must have lost it.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Fried_Fish_a_la_Ridge.Name: Fried Fish a la Ridge
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Fried_Fish_a_la_Ridge.Description: A Pika special! The rich umami flavor is paired with crispy and salty breading.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Fried_Mountain_Greens.Name: Fried Mountain Greens
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Fried_Mountain_Greens.Description: Fried vegetables have never been so tasty!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Frost_Clump_Berry.Name: Frost Clump Berry
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Frost_Clump_Berry.Description: A strange berry that only seems to ripen when covered in snow. It tastes like grape with a hint of melon.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ginger_Arugula_Fried_Rice.Name: Ginger Arugula Fried Rice
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ginger_Arugula_Fried_Rice.Description: A steaming bowl of vegetable fried rice seasoned with ginger. Good for the stomach if you're feeling under the weather.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ginger_Rangpur_Meringue.Name: Ginger Rangpur Meringue
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ginger_Rangpur_Meringue.Description: A dessert that combines the boldness of ginger and rangpur with the lightness of meringue. Despite its richness, it's good for digestion.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Glove_of_the_Assassin.Name: Glove of the Assassin
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Glove_of_the_Assassin.Description: Makes you invisible to enemies until you are directly in their field of vision. (Wear in ring slot.)

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Golden_Rose_Fin.Name: Golden Rose Fin
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Golden_Rose_Fin.Description: A small fish with wide, yet thin fins. As it swims, the movement of these unique fins lend an appearance of dancing as it twirls and moves across the water.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Golden_Skull_Coral.Name: Golden Skull Coral
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Golden_Skull_Coral.Description: A golden statue replica of an extinct species of coral from the ancient era.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Harvester_Trout.Name: Harvester Trout
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Harvester_Trout.Description: It got its name for 'harvesting' crops and plants that grow near water. This destructive behavior has led to this fish being regarded as a pest. Despite this, it remains popular due to its tender, oily meat.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Blueberry_Pie.Name: Highland Blueberry Pie
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Blueberry_Pie.Description: Despite what its name may suggest, it gets the blue out of you!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Butterwort.Name: Highland Butterwort
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Butterwort.Description: Kids love to use this in local games!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Chard.Name: Highland Chard
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Chard.Description: A leafy green mostly found along mountain ridges. Has a delicate, yet sharp taste that turns bitter when the weather gets too hot. Commonly used in salads.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Ice_Cream.Name: Highland Ice Cream
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Ice_Cream.Description: Special ice cream made in Ridgeside Village. A treat best enjoyed while admiring the mountainside view.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Jostaberry.Name: Highland Jostaberry
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Highland_Jostaberry.Description: Resembling a gooseberry and black currant fused into one, this variant has evolved into being grown in trees and common in cold continents.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Holiday_Ice.Name: Holiday Ice
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Holiday_Ice.Description: Ice cream made from an exotic tropical fruit! It even has a little umbrella for that extra tropical feel.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Hollowed_Bear.Name: Hollowed Bear
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Hollowed_Bear.Description: It looks like an old teddy bear. What's weird is the exterior is rigid and it's hollowed out inside.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Honey_Ginger_Whitefish.Name: Honey Ginger Whitefish
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Honey_Ginger_Whitefish.Description: Mountain whitefish marinated in a classic sweet-sharp sauce. It's surprisingly gentle on the stomach.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Honey_Glazed_Salad.Name: Honey Glazed Salad
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Honey_Glazed_Salad.Description: Pika's special salad, glazed with homemade honey. Super sweet!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Inked_Fossil.Name: Inked Fossil
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Inked_Fossil.Description: The dragon-like skull print in the fossil seems to be outlined by some sort of permanent ink. What's odd is the ink seems fresh for something ancient.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Kedi_Delight.Name: Kedi Delight
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Kedi_Delight.Description: A sweet confection made of starch and sugar, often made with unique flavors.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Kek_s_Small_Dream.Name: Kek's Small Dream
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Kek_s_Small_Dream.Description: Like the big one, just less.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Kek_s_Style_Shortcake.Name: Kek's Style Shortcake
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Kek_s_Style_Shortcake.Description: A sweet treat! Who shaved that strawberry though?

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Lava_Lily.Name: Lava Lily
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Lava_Lily.Description: It emits a warm sensation. A nice flower to hold in the cold.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Lover_s_Sorrow.Name: Lover's Sorrow
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Lover_s_Sorrow.Description: Mystery surrounds this stone sculpture of a rose. Some say it's a petrified ancient flower. Whatever the case is, this object has been linked with misfortunes that have befallen upon couples that had this in their possession.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Lullaby_Carp.Name: Lullaby Carp
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Lullaby_Carp.Description: A scientific mystery. When left alone, this fish produces soothing tunes, yet it does not possess any internal system that would allow it to 'sing'.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Matcha_Latte.Name: Matcha Latte
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Matcha_Latte.Description: Coffee and green tea live in perfect harmony.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mistbloom_Syrup.Name: Mistbloom Syrup
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mistbloom_Syrup.Description: Squeezed nectar from Mountain Mistblooms, this strange liquid can help cure nausea.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Moose_Statue.Name: Moose Statue
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Moose_Statue.Description: A sculpture of a long-forgotten deity.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Arugula.Name: Mountain Arugula
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Arugula.Description: A cool-weather crop found in mountain ridges. According to the locals, it gives a temporary boost in luck.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Chico.Name: Mountain Chico
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Chico.Description: An unusual fruit that differs from its relatives. This variety grows on wild bushes instead of trees.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Hokkaido.Name: Mountain Hokkaido
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Hokkaido.Description: The beauty it has suites well with mountain breeze.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Mistbloom.Name: Mountain Mistbloom
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Mistbloom.Description: A mysterious glowing flower that bloom during rainy days in the dense mountain forest. It doesn't emit any kind of smell at all.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Plumcot.Name: Mountain Plumcot
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Plumcot.Description: A perfectly even blend of plum and apricot only found in the mountains of eastern continents. Some even say that they're stone fruits.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Redbelly_Dace.Name: Mountain Redbelly Dace
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Redbelly_Dace.Description: An elusive species, and quite a challenge to reel in. Its meat is quite tasty!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Whitefish.Name: Mountain Whitefish
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Mountain_Whitefish.Description: Despite reflecting light easily, its agile and irregular movements make it surprisingly hard to catch.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Nightblack_Diamond.Name: Nightblack Diamond
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Nightblack_Diamond.Description: An sharp edged diamond with a black tint. The base barely reflects any light, so make sure you don't lose it in the dark.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Northern_Limequat.Name: Northern Limequat
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Northern_Limequat.Description: Often a substitute for lemons or key limes, but don't underestimate this northern-bound fruit! Because of the natural habitat's high state, this has been made perfect to balance sweet recipes.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Old_Lucky_Foxtail_Charm.Name: Old Lucky Foxtail Charm
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Old_Lucky_Foxtail_Charm.Description: A bracelet that used to belong to your grandmother.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Opal_Halo.Name: Opal Halo
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Opal_Halo.Description: A piece of ancient headgear with embedded opal stones. There's a carving of an angel on the side.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Pale_Candelabrum.Name: Pale Candelabrum
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Pale_Candelabrum.Description: The candles are lined with skull patterns. The wick seems to be moist, making it difficult to light the candles.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Paradise_Rangpur.Name: Paradise Rangpur
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Paradise_Rangpur.Description: Once you taste this, it'll definitely take you to paradise with its intensely sour and smoky lime flavor! Perfect for classy delicacies.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Pebble_Back_Crab.Name: Pebble Back Crab
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Pebble_Back_Crab.Description: The pebbles adorning its back are collected by the fish while young, serving as defense and camouflage. Some accidentally collect gemstones, and thus are overhunted by humans.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Pink_Frosted_Sprinkled_Do.Name: Pink Frosted Sprinkled Doughnut
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Pink_Frosted_Sprinkled_Do.Description: This must be what rainbows are made of.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Relic_Fox_Mask.Name: Relic Fox Mask
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Relic_Fox_Mask.Description: An ancient mask that resembles a fox. There's a text written around the rim of the eyehole: 'Rough Seas'.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Richard_s_Glasses.Name: Richard's Glasses
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Richard_s_Glasses.Description: Richard's glasses! He must have lost them.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Apple_Cake.Name: Ridge Apple Cake
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Apple_Cake.Description: Sweet and comforting to the core!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Azorean_Flower.Name: Ridge Azorean Flower
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Azorean_Flower.Description: The spring smells lovelier because of this flower.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Bluegill.Name: Ridge Bluegill
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Bluegill.Description: It blends well with the river water! Don't lose sight of it!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Cherry.Name: Ridge Cherry
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Cherry.Description: A type of cherry found near mountain ridges. Presents a tangy, sweet flavor.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Fruity_Plate.Name: Ridge Fruity Plate
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Fruity_Plate.Description: A fruit salad filled with mountain fruits, topped with a special dressing!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Mosaic_Cake.Name: Ridge Mosaic Cake
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Mosaic_Cake.Description: A sweet treat made up of cocoa and biscuits.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Wild_Apple.Name: Ridge Wild Apple
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridge_Wild_Apple.Description: A type of apple that has small red spines along its skin. It tastes identical to pineapple—the main difference being there is a little less of it to eat.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridgeside_Bass.Name: Ridgeside Bass
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridgeside_Bass.Description: A mountain fish native to Ridgeside Village.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridgeside_Clementine.Name: Ridgeside Clementine
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridgeside_Clementine.Description: Much like a regular clementine; the difference is its nutty aftertaste. The cold winter climate and high altitude prevent this fruit from rotting too quickly.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridgeside_Monkshood.Name: Ridgeside Monkshood
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Ridgeside_Monkshood.Description: It calms even the crankiest of men.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Sapphire_Pearl.Name: Sapphire Pearl
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Sapphire_Pearl.Description: An ancient relic of the ridge. It's a unique amalgamation of a sapphire gem and a pearl.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Shell_Bracelet.Name: Shell Bracelet
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Shell_Bracelet.Description: The smell of the ocean still lingers in this ancient accessory. A foreign text is engraved in the shell's rim.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Sierra_Wintergreen.Name: Sierra Wintergreen
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Sierra_Wintergreen.Description: A lovely flower to gift and decorate during the winter holidays.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Silver_Fish_Bones.Name: Silver Fish Bones
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Silver_Fish_Bones.Description: A mysterious relic of silver bones resembling the shape of a fish embedded in ancient stone.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Skulpin_Fish.Name: Skulpin Fish
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Skulpin_Fish.Description: The spines around its fins are soft unless startled. So be gentle.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Snow_Bowl_Surprise.Name: Snow Bowl Surprise
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Snow_Bowl_Surprise.Description: Local wild fruit, paired with clean ice shavings, syrup and cherries.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Snowball_Slurpee.Name: Snowball Slurpee
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Snowball_Slurpee.Description: A mix of different winter fruits. A cool and sweet winter treat.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Sockeye_Salmon.Name: Sockeye Salmon
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Sockeye_Salmon.Description: The sought after legendary fish of Ridgeside Village! It's docile and likes to eat cherries!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Spiritual_Essence.Name: Spiritual Essence
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Spiritual_Essence.Description: A mysterious collection of pebbles glowing dim.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Springtime_Primetime.Name: Springtime Primetime
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Springtime_Primetime.Description: Pika's spring special. Your appetite blossoms as you gaze at it.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Strawberry_Lover_Pie.Name: Strawberry Lover Pie
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Strawberry_Lover_Pie.Description: It makes you feel a little special inside, you berry cute thing.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Summer_Mountain_Blessing.Name: Summer Mountain Blessing
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Summer_Mountain_Blessing.Description: Pika's summer special. The dish that warms you up, in a good way!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Summit_Snowbell.Name: Summit Snowbell
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Summit_Snowbell.Description: It's a local sign that winter is coming!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Sweet_Cranberry_Cheesecak.Name: Sweet Cranberry Cheesecake
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Sweet_Cranberry_Cheesecak.Description: A berry cute sweet for a berry cute person.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Tropi_Ugli_Fruit.Name: Tropi Ugli Fruit
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Tropi_Ugli_Fruit.Description: Don't get fooled by its name, this is a beautiful and tasty fruit that's sweet and tart with a hint of sharpness. Definitely worth trying! Isn't it a beaut?

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Tropic_Mango_Cake.Name: Tropic Mango Cake
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Tropic_Mango_Cake.Description: Made from mangoes, this cake is mango-neficient!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Village_Hero_Sculpture.Name: Village Hero Sculpture
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Village_Hero_Sculpture.Description: A vaguely familiar figure. This relic is covered in moss yet the material that makes up the object doesn't show signs of breaking.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Violet_Devil_s_Claw.Name: Violet Devil's Claw
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Violet_Devil_s_Claw.Description: It's alluring scent and aesthetic makes it popular for perfumes and decorations.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Warp_Totem__Ridgeside.Name: Warp Totem: Ridgeside
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Warp_Totem__Ridgeside.Description: Warp directly to Ridgeside Village. Consumed on use.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Waterfall_Snakehead.Name: Waterfall Snakehead
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Waterfall_Snakehead.Description: Its snake-like head has adapted to be hard as a boulder due to the extreme force of waterfalls around its habitat. It's one of the legendary fishes of the ridge!

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Winter_Night_Feast.Name: Winter Night Feast
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Winter_Night_Feast.Description: Pika's winter special. The meal that keeps on giving, or so they say.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Yellow_Wood_Sculpture.Name: Yellow Wood Sculpture
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Yellow_Wood_Sculpture.Description: The ancient figure's face looks vaguely familiar. But you can't put a put a finger on who it is.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Yuuma_s_Ring.Name: Yuuma's Ring
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Yuuma_s_Ring.Description: Yuuma's ring! He must have lost it.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_Zesty_Tuna.Name: Zesty Tuna
Rafseazz.RSVCP_Zesty_Tuna.Description: Smoked tuna with citrus sauce! It's a Ridgeside specialty.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_The_Beautiful_Serpent_s_R.Name: The Beautiful Serpent's Ring
Rafseazz.RSVCP_The_Beautiful_Serpent_s_R.Description: Summons a soul from the Spirit Realm to your side.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_The_Fairy_Doe_Fox_s_Ring.Name: The Fairy Doe Fox's Ring
Rafseazz.RSVCP_The_Fairy_Doe_Fox_s_Ring.Description: Summons a fox spirit to your side.

Rafseazz.RSVCP_The_Ring_of_the_Ridge_Dei.Name: The Ring of the Ridge Deities
Rafseazz.RSVCP_The_Ring_of_the_Ridge_Dei.DisplayName: The Ring of the Ridge Deities

LASV_Dewdrop_Fish.Name: Dewdrop Fish
LASV_Dewdrop_Fish.Description: An ancient fish named for its shape.

LASV_Purple_Spotted_Trout.Name: Purple Spotted Trout
LASV_Purple_Spotted_Trout.Description: A freshwater fish not found in the human world.

LASV_Relicantlette.Name: Relicantlette
LASV_Relicantlette.Description: A common fish found in ancient lakes.

LASV_Serafin.Name: Serafin
LASV_Serafin.Description: A pretty fish with wing-like fins.

LASV_Umuwi_Carp.Name: Umuwi Carp
LASV_Umuwi_Carp.Description: A rare fish found in Umuwi. It seems to radiate magic.

LASV_Umuwi_Aster.Name: Umuwi Aster
LASV_Umuwi_Aster.Description: A local fall flower that blooms in Umuwi. Comes in many colors.

LASV_Umuwi_Badak.Name: Umuwi Badak
LASV_Umuwi_Badak.Description: An ovate orange yam. Has a sweet flavor with a touch of chestnut.

LASV_Umuwi_Calamansi.Name: Umuwi Calamansi
LASV_Umuwi_Calamansi.Description: A small round citrus fruit that is found in the fields of Umuwi all year round.

LASV_Umuwi_Makahiya.Name: Umuwi Makahiya
LASV_Umuwi_Makahiya.Description: A thorny flower with leaves that shuts close whenever it is touched.

LASV_Umuwi_Olive.Name: Umuwi Olive
LASV_Umuwi_Olive.Description: A variant of olive that has a spicy aftertaste!

LASV_Umuwi_Poinsettia.Name: Umuwi Poinsettia
LASV_Umuwi_Poinsettia.Description: A flower that blooms in the cold dirt of Umuwi. Popular among female shadow-folk and werewolves.

LASV_Umuwi_Sampaguita.Name: Umuwi Sampaguita
LASV_Umuwi_Sampaguita.Description: A local summer flower that blooms in Umuwi. Has a faint fragrance to it.

LASV_Eggroot.Name: Eggroot
LASV_Eggroot.Description: An egg-shaped root crop that has a rich and savory flavor.

LASV_Ghost_Cabbage.Name: Ghost Cabbage
LASV_Ghost_Cabbage.Description: You can almost see through its leaves.

LASV_Pale_Berry.Name: Pale Berry
LASV_Pale_Berry.Description: A pale purple-colored berry that has a soothing sweet aftertaste.

LASV_Sour_Potato.Name: Sour Potato
LASV_Sour_Potato.Description: A variation of potato grown in Umuwi. It tastes sour.

LASV_Thorn_Pepper.Name: Thorn Pepper
LASV_Thorn_Pepper.Description: A thorny and bitter species of pepper.

LASV_Umuwi_Lanzones.Name: Umuwi Lanzones
LASV_Umuwi_Lanzones.Description: A small fruit high in antioxidants, vitamins, and protein.

LASV_Umuwi_Rambutan.Name: Umuwi Rambutan
LASV_Umuwi_Rambutan.Description: A red, plum-sized fruit with soft spines and a slightly acidic taste.

LASV_EmbraceFruit.Name: EmbraceFruit
LASV_EmbraceFruit.Description: A fruit as warm as Bianka's presence. It seems to reduce pain for a few seconds.

LASV_HastePill.Name: HastePill
LASV_HastePill.Description: A magic pill of haste formulated by Raphael and you. It gives extreme speed for a few seconds.

LASV_LuckyMint.Name: LuckyMint
LASV_LuckyMint.Description: A mint candy imbued with Lunna's ancient magic. It increases luck dramatically for a short period of time.

LASV_Pale_Berry_Pie.Name: Pale Berry Pie
LASV_Pale_Berry_Pie.Description: A pie filled with Umuwi's Pale Berries. It has a very sweet aftertaste!

LASV_Sour_Hashbrown.Name: Sour Hashbrown
LASV_Sour_Hashbrown.Description: A unique-tasting potato made into a hash brown!

LASV_Umuwi_Mash.Name: Umuwi Mash
LASV_Umuwi_Mash.Description: A spicy and starchy mash good for a cold winter day!

LASV_Umuwi_Salad.Name: Umuwi Salad
LASV_Umuwi_Salad.Description: A salad made with Umuwi produce. It has a sweet savory taste!

LASV_Eggroot_Seeds.Name: Eggroot Seeds
LASV_Eggroot_Seeds.Description: Plant in spring. It takes 14 days to produce Eggroot.

LASV_Ghost_Cabbage_Seeds.Name: Ghost Cabbage Seeds
LASV_Ghost_Cabbage_Seeds.Description: Plant in the fall. It takes 8 days to produce Ghost Cabbage.

LASV_Pale_Berry_Seeds.Name: Pale Berry Seeds
LASV_Pale_Berry_Seeds.Description: Plant in spring. It takes 6 days to produce Pale Berries and regrows after harvest.

LASV_Sour_Potato_Seeds.Name: Sour Potato Seeds
LASV_Sour_Potato_Seeds.Description: Plant in the summer. It takes 8 days to produce Sour Potato.

LASV_Thorn_Pepper_Seeds.Name: Thorn Pepper Seeds
LASV_Thorn_Pepper_Seeds.Description: Plant in the summer. It takes 10 days to produce Thorn Peppers and regrows after harvest.

LASV_Umuwi_Lanzones_Sapling.Name: Umuwi Lanzones Sapling
LASV_Umuwi_Lanzones_Sapling.Description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Lanzones tree. Ready to harvest in the summer. Only grows if the 8 surrounding tiles are empty.

LASV_Umuwi_Rambutan_Sapling.Name: Umuwi Rambutan Sapling
LASV_Umuwi_Rambutan_Sapling.Description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Rambutan tree. Ready to harvest in the spring. Only grows if the 8 surrounding tiles are empty.

7thAxis.DitR_Items.SensCrocus.Name: 7thAxis.LitD.CP_Items.SensCrocus
7thAxis.DitR_Items.SensCrocus.Description: This item has no functionality unless you have seen Sen's 14h event. It is only loaded for mod compatibility.

nachonline.mps_GreenSlimeCheese.Description: Cheese made with green slime. It's very gooey.

nachonline.mps_TigerSlimeCheese.Description: Cheese made with tiger slime. It's very gooey.

nachonline.mps_MineralWater.Name: nachonline.mps_MineralWater
nachonline.mps_MineralWater.Description: Remember: drink 3 of these every day.

nachonline.mps_DuckCloth.Name: nachonline.mps_DuckCloth
nachonline.mps_DuckCloth.Description: A bolt of fine duck feather cloth.

nachonline.mps_OstrichMayonnaise.Name: nachonline.mps_OstrichMayonnaise
nachonline.mps_OstrichMayonnaise.Description: It's thick and creamy, with pink undertones. It smells like grass and clean air.

Meara.Roosters_FertEggBrown.Description: There seems to be something inside!

Meara.Roosters_FertEggGold.Description: There seems to be something inside!

Meara.RoostersLargegoldEgg.Description: It's an uncommonly large golden egg!

Meara.RoostersLargevoidEgg.Description: A large jet-black egg with red flecks. It's warm to the touch.

Meara.RoostersLargeBlueEgg.Name: Large Blue Egg
Meara.RoostersLargeBlueEgg.Description: It's an uncommonly large blue egg!

b42ti0n.CP.LitW_Bagseed.Description: It's a clear bag full of unkown genetics, only one way to find out.

b42ti0n.CP.LitW_Shatter.Description: A cannabis concentrate that has a glass like texture.

b42ti0n.CP.LitW_BluntDitchweed.Description: A little heftier than a joint, maybe share with a friend.

Cornucopia_WolfsbaneSeeds.Name: Cornucopia_WolfsbaneSeeds
Cornucopia_WolfsbaneSeeds.Description: Plant these in summer. Takes 13 days to mature.

Cornucopia_CorpseFlowerSeed.Name: Cornucopia_CorpseFlowerSeed
Cornucopia_CorpseFlowerSeed.Description: The seed of a stinking flower as large as a tree.

Cornucopia_Hibiscus.Name: Cornucopia_Hibiscus
Cornucopia_Hibiscus.Description: A bright red flower that grows best in a tropical climate. It smells very sweet.

Cornucopia_Jasmine.Name: Cornucopia_Jasmine
Cornucopia_Jasmine.Description: These are sweet, highly scented flowers.

Cornucopia_Magnolia.Name: Cornucopia_Magnolia
Cornucopia_Magnolia.Description: An elegant flower that grows on a shady tree.

Cornucopia_Wisteria.Name: Cornucopia_Wisteria
Cornucopia_Wisteria.Description: An especially fragrant cluster of purple flowers.

Cornucopia_YlangYlang.Name: Cornucopia_YlangYlang
Cornucopia_YlangYlang.Description: A highly appreciated flower in perfumery and aromatherapy.

Cornucopia_HibiscusSapling.Name: Cornucopia_HibiscusSapling
Cornucopia_HibiscusSapling.Description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Hibiscus tree. Blossoms in the summer. Only grows if the 8 surrounding tiles are empty.

Cornucopia_JasmineSapling.Name: Cornucopia_JasmineSapling
Cornucopia_JasmineSapling.Description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Jasmine tree. Blossoms in the fall. Only grows if the 8 surrounding tiles are empty.

Cornucopia_MagnoliaSapling.Name: Cornucopia_MagnoliaSapling
Cornucopia_MagnoliaSapling.Description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Magnolia tree. Blossoms in the spring. Only grows if the 8 surrounding tiles are empty.

Cornucopia_WisteriaSapling.Name: Cornucopia_WisteriaSapling
Cornucopia_WisteriaSapling.Description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Wisteria tree. Blossoms in the spring. Only grows if the 8 surrounding "tiles" are empty.

Cornucopia_YlangYlangSapling.Name: Cornucopia_YlangYlangSapling
Cornucopia_YlangYlangSapling.Description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Ylang Ylang tree. Blossoms in the summer. Only grows if the 8 surrounding "tiles" are empty.

bonghits.Cp_BearHoneyMead.Name: bonghits.Cp_BearHoneyMead
bonghits.Cp_BearHoneyMead.Description: An artisanal mead crafted to perfection using Honey harvested by happy Bears.

bonghits.Cp_AgedBearHoneyMead.Name: bonghits.Cp_AgedBearHoneyMead
bonghits.Cp_AgedBearHoneyMead.Description: An artisanal bear honey mead refined and aged to its highest potential. The fruity smell eminating from the bottle reminds you of a warm bath in the spring.

Mizu.Turkey_TurkeyFeather.Name: Mizu.Turkey_TurkeyFeather
Mizu.Turkey_TurkeyFeather.Description: A broad plume from the tail of a turkey.

Mizu.Turkey_TurkeyMayonnaise.Name: Mizu.Turkey_TurkeyMayonnaise
Mizu.Turkey_TurkeyMayonnaise.Description: Seems like it would be great on a fall sandwich.

WWWA.AutographedPhoto.Name: WWWA.AutographedPhoto
WWWA.AutographedPhoto.Description: An autographed photo of two-time award winner, author Rodney O'Brien.

WWWA.GenuineAutograph.Name: WWWA.GenuineAutograph
WWWA.GenuineAutograph.Description: This looks like an original autographed photo of two-time award winner, author Rodney O'Brien.
